title.undefined: Ontology for Digital Markers in Mental Health (ODIM-MH)

description.undefined: Ontology for organizing measurements, features, context, provenance, and digital phenotypes for wearable/device-based health studies.

title.value: Ontology for Digital Markers in Mental Health (ODIM-MH)

comment.undefined: Higher-level construct inferred from features and measurements.
Layer for raw observations/measurements captured from devices and apps.
A process or activity that computes features or infers phenotypes.
Layer for features derived from measurements.
Software interface used to capture or transfer data.
An attribute computed from one or more measurements.
A meta-class grouping the modeling layers in this ontology.
An individual taking part in a study.
A hardware or software platform used to collect data.
A collection of data items associated with a participant or study process.
A feature computed from raw measurements and possibly other features.
An activity/process that captures sensor data and produces measurements.
A single observation or data point recorded by a device or system.

IAO_0000115.value: A single observation recorded by a device or system, optionally linked to a QUDT QuantityValue and SOSA properties.

comment.undefined: Associates a dataset with the participant it was collected from.
Links an entity to an agent it is attributed to (e.g., a dataset to a participant).
Links an entity (e.g., measurement/feature/dataset) to the computation/activity that generated it.
Indicates a measurement used in computing a feature.
Associates an activity/computation with a device agent.
